gw.plugin.policyperiod

Interface IEffectiveTimePlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public interface IEffectiveTimePlugin
extends com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin

    Determines the initial time component of a PolicyPeriod's effective/expiration dates (a.k.a. PeriodStart/PeriodEnd dates) when starting a new job. The affected jobs are:

    • Submission
    • PolicyChange
    • Cancellation
    • Reinstatement
    • Rewrite
    • RewriteNewAccount
    • Renewal

    There are no hooks for the Issuance job, since because it is logically seen as a continuation/completion of Submission, its PolicyPeriod simply inherits the dates as set by the Submission job.

    Similarly, there are no hooks for the Audit job, since it simply uses the dates of the PolicyPeriod being audited.

    All of this interface's methods have a PolicyPeriod parameter, which can be used to access additional information that might be used to determine the desired time, such as:

    • the line(s) of business
    • the base state
    • other revisions
    • etc.

    The return value from each of this interface's methods should be a Date, with its time component, HH:mm:ss, set to the desired time; the day component, dd/MM/yyyy, is ignored. As a convenience, null can be returned to leave the time component set to the default (midnight).
